7496,bug: Silent failure when data.getLength fails in Node http adapter,2026-03-13 14:46:42+00:00,2026-03-15 11:09:10+00:00,closed,4,['issue::bug'],"## Summary
In the Node.js http adapter, when using the form-data package, Axios attempts to calculate the Content-Length using data.getLength. However, the current implementation wraps this call in a silent try...catch block.

If getLength fails (e.g., due to an issue with a file stream inside the form), the catch block silently swallows the error, and the request proceeds without a Content-Length header. This often results in a 411 Length Required or a mysterious 400 Bad Request from servers, m"
