6919,When a request fails an autheorization header may be part of the error and may get logged,2025-05-28 11:01:14+00:00,2025-06-01 16:23:19+00:00,closed,3,[],"### Describe the bug

When making a request with Axios, if the request fails (e.g., with a 403 Forbidden), Axios throws an error that includes the full request config—including the Authorization header—in the error object.

This is the default behavior and poses a security risk, especially when error objects are logged or exposed in other ways. Sensitive information such as bearer tokens should never be included in errors by default.

Expected behavior:
Axios should redact or omit sensitive head"
