4586,optimize some code,2022-04-06 14:33:48+00:00,2022-04-06 14:34:27+00:00,closed,1,[],"The following line of code comes from https://github.com/axios/axios/blob/master/lib/adapters/http.js#L403:
```js
reject(!cancel || (cancel && cancel.type) ? new CanceledError() : cancel);
```
If `!cancel` is false, it means cancel is not false. So it can be optimized as follows:
```js
reject(!cancel || cancel.type ? new CanceledError() : cancel);
```"
