1609,dispatchRequest mutates `config` object,2018-06-16 15:30:11+00:00,2020-05-21 17:51:52+00:00,closed,1,[],"<!-- Click ""Preview"" for a more readable version -->

#### Summary

`dispatchRequest` mutates `config` object, which may confuse developers during debugging. 
Also, mutation is not recommended generally.

Consider this example:

```
axios.interceptors.request.use(function(config) {
  console.log(config);
  return config;
});
```

In this case `console.log` will log already mutated config (e.g. `headers` will be flattened object).
But it should log the actual value of `config` be"
