1483,"Url encoding of backtick (""`"") character in query strings",2018-04-14 07:21:21+00:00,2020-05-21 17:49:46+00:00,closed,1,[],"#### Summary

This issue is the same as https://github.com/visionmedia/superagent/issues/1367, and is driven by the same underlying cause (reliance on the built-in `url.parse`) and has the same basic fix (surfacing the WHATWG URL api). 

Code example is just:

```
axios.get('http://example.com/?test=`value`')
```

Result: backticks around ""value"" get percent-encoded, arguably improperly and with no way to override. See linked issue for details.

#### Context

- axios version: v0.18"
