1181,Memory leak caused by CancelToken,2017-11-15 10:53:16+00:00,2018-07-09 02:33:45+00:00,closed,3,[],"#### Summary

 If the token does not cancel, the promise in token will reference to all instances of `XMLHttpRequest` even they are already resolved. So if using same cancel token to get data repeatedly, the token will keep all the request instances, which caused memory leak. 
The reference looks like: `source -> token -> promise -> OnCancel() context -> request`

If someone want to avoid this, he/she need set `source = null` after all the request returned, and may not use interval + single"
